    \item \textbf{Cryptographic Utility:} In practice, this allows a cloud server to ``rotate'' data slots (shifting index $i$ to index $k \cdot i$) purely in its encrypted form. Because Lean 4 is a dependent type theory, proving this theorem ensures that the Galois-key switching logic in an FHE implementation is mathematically sound and free of off-by-one errors.
